Tigers will and do regularly prey on humans, because individually, we aren't very strong, which is why we probably developed social skills in the first place. What places us at the top of the food chain is our ability to reason and plan, and predict the results of our actions.<br>
Pretty amazing when you think of it, that we have evolved so much that our enviroment no longer plays a role in our species development, because we force our enviroment to change to suit us. <br>
Being omnivorous gives us more food choices, we are not a niche species. We are the Bard of this planet. If Vegans feel the need to restrict their diet to only part of the available food scource, that's a choice they were designed by nature to make. I don't personally agree with it, but I'll defend, to the death, their right to make a choice.<br>
